# Shell scripts must stay LF, even when checked out on Windows. The simulator validation and container
# scripts run under bash (in WSL or a Linux container), and a CRLF line ending turns `set -euo pipefail`
# into `pipefail\r` -- "invalid option name" -- which is exactly how the capacity harness failed to start
# on a Windows checkout. Pin the ending so a clone cannot reintroduce it.
*.sh text eol=lf
